{
  "text": "We took a thermodynamic approach to capacitor failure, using the first and second laws of thermodynamics [CITATION_1] with in a non-equilibrium system considering the approximation of local equilibrium. The dot over the variable represents a time derivative, i.e., . In (3), U, W, Q, and E irr are the internal, stored, heat and irreversible damage energies, respectively. In (4), subindices e and i refer to external (entropy exchange) and internal entropy (entropy generation), respectively [CITATION_2] ; thus, entropy remains a valuable state function. We are interested in , includes thermal dissipation and ageing, and must be positive. The stored energy (dW) for a capacitor is well-known and described by the following:",
